While both Skilling and Enron Chairman Ken Lay, former -- and now current --=
 president and CEO, maintain that Skilling left for personal reasons and of =
his own volition, the shroud of secrecy over the specifics is troubling to b=
oth investors and pundits -- including my colleague James J. Cramer. </rmone=
y/jamesjcramer/1518948.html>=20
On a company conference call Tuesday evening, Skilling said he "wished to ke=
